<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p><table class=3D"header" =
width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Activism</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way activist investing works in th=
e U.S. is generally that an activist investor quietly buys up a chunk of a =
company=E2=80=99s stock, announces that she owns the stock, and goes to the=
 company=E2=80=99s managers asking them to change something about their str=
ategy or operations. Sometimes the managers agree,=C2=A0there is a producti=
ve conversation,=C2=A0the activist helps the company improve, the stock goe=
s up and eventually the activist sells at a profit. Sometimes the managers =
disagree, and the activist tries to pressure them into doing what she wants=
. She might wage a public campaign, writing open letters explaining her pos=
ition. She might talk to other shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0big institutiona=
l holders who don=E2=80=99t wage activist campaigns themselves but who own =
a lot of stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0to persuade them that she is right. If lots o=
f shareholders agree with her, but the managers still don=E2=80=99t, she mi=
ght launch a proxy fight: She will nominate some people to the company=E2=
=80=99s board of directors and try to get them elected to replace some of t=
he existing directors. If enough other shareholders vote with her, her cand=
idates will win and join the board and presumably do the things she wants. =
Hopefully the things she wants are good and the stock will go up and she wi=
ll sell at a profit.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sometimes this doesn=
=E2=80=99t work: Managers ignore the activist, other shareholders disagree =
with her, she loses the proxy fight, etc. Other times it sort of works, but=
 is bad: The company does what the activist wants, or at least enough to ma=
ke shareholders satisfied, but it turns out to be wrong and the stock goes =
down.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In general though it seems obviously =
good that activism=C2=A0<em>exists</em>. For one thing, it often does make =
companies more valuable: An activist shareholder, who owns a big chunk of t=
he company and only makes money if the stock goes up, will sometimes have b=
etter incentives and motivations than a chief executive officer who owns le=
ss of the company and collects a large salary even if the stock goes down.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">More fundamentally, though, activism is one=
 of the few ways that shareholders can exercise real power over the compani=
es that they theoretically own. As we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/27137501.259601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvZXh4b24tbG9zdC1hLWNsaW1hdGUtcHJveHktZmlnaH=
Q_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlP=
W5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB73dfaa88" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> often discuss around here</a>, if a co=
mpany=E2=80=99s board and managers want to ignore their shareholders, they =
mostly can. The only ways that shareholders in the U.S. can actually=C2=A0<=
em>fire=C2=A0</em>the board and CEO=C2=A0of a public company are (1) a prox=
y fight or (2) a hostile takeover.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They don=
=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>that very often. But this is the=C2=A0<em>=
background=C2=A0</em>that makes other, softer forms of pressure work. If Bl=
ackRock Inc. calls up a company and says =E2=80=9Cwe are a big shareholder =
and we=E2=80=99d like you to reduce your greenhouse gas emissions,=E2=80=9D=
 the executives will generally listen to BlackRock and care what it thinks,=
 because they know that, if they don=E2=80=99t, BlackRock will become disgr=
untled, and if enough big shareholders become disgruntled enough an activis=
t might show up and win a proxy fight. (Sometimes the disgruntled big insti=
tutional shareholders will quietly=C2=A0<em>invite=C2=A0</em>an activist to=
 show up; this is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
27137501.259601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMTQtMDMtMTkvYWN0aXZpc3QtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtYXJlLW1ha2luZy1mcmllbmRzP2NtcGlkPU=
JCRDAzMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0d=
GVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDMyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB5d4b3e35" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> informally called</a> an =E2=80=9CRFA,=E2=80=9D =
or =E2=80=9Crequest for activist.=E2=80=9D) There just isn=E2=80=99t that m=
uch that BlackRock can do on its own: The board controls the company, board=
 elections are not competitive (outside of proxy fights)=C2=A0and most of w=
hat shareholders vote on is non-binding; BlackRock has a lot of shares, and=
 so a lot of votes, but it can't do much with them. But if an activist show=
s up, BlackRock =E2=80=94=C2=A0or other shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0can vot=
e out the board. And the managers know that, which is why they feel the nee=
d to keep shareholders happy.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CKeep=
 shareholders happy=E2=80=9D is a very generic goal. Historically it meant =
things like having high profits. Later it meant things like doing stock buy=
backs. Increasingly, it means doing good environmental, social and governan=
ce things, as big shareholders become more diversified and more focused on =
ESG. And when companies=C2=A0<em>don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>do the ESG things =
that shareholders want, there will be <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/27137501.259601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMjgvZGFuLWxvZWItd2FudHMtYS1jbGVhbi1zaGVsbC1hbm=
QtYS1kaXJ0eS1zaGVsbD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMzI0MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtY=
WlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjAzMjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1v=
bmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdce306fc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> ESG activists</a> a=
nd <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27137501.259601=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMjcvZX=
h4b24tbG9zdC1hLWNsaW1hdGUtcHJveHktZmlnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVR=
kYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMzI0=
JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC73dfaa88" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
> proxy fights</a>, because activism is the enforcement mechanism that shar=
eholders use to influence companies.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Recent=
ly, though, the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission has proposed some r=
ules to =E2=80=A6=C2=A0stop activism? This seems bad, and also like a stran=
ge priority for the SEC to have.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even stran=
ger is SEC Chair Gary Gensler=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/27137501.259601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDEtMjAvYS1nb29kLXJlcHV0YXRpb24taXMtZXhwZW5zaXZl=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMjQyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDMyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cBf24b6dc0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> stated reason for getting rid of activ=
ism</a>. Gensler thinks activism is bad because:</p><ul style=3D"list-style=
-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">Activists buy stock in the target company quietly,=C2=A0<em>bef=
ore=C2=A0</em>they do activism;</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Wh=
en they do activism =E2=80=94=C2=A0or even when they just announce their pl=
ans to do activism, or just announce that they bought stock =E2=80=94 the s=
tock goes up;</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The people who=C2=A0=
<em>sold=C2=A0</em>them their stock, before the activism, don=E2=80=99t get=
 the benefit of that stock-price increase.</li></ul><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
