ubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xM2QtNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cBffc93ee5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">defines a =E2=80=9Cgroup=E2=80=9D</a>:</p><blockquote><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When two or more persons agree to act together =
for the purpose of acquiring, holding, voting or disposing of equity securi=
ties of an issuer, the group formed thereby shall be deemed to have acquire=
d beneficial ownership, for purposes of sections 13(d) and (g) of the Act, =
as of the date of such agreement, of all equity securities of that issuer b=
eneficially owned by any such persons.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/27137501.259601/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9ydWxlcy9wcm9wb3NlZC8yMD=
IyLzMzLTExMDMwLnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCb19847d9" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">new proposa=
l</a> would get rid of the words =E2=80=9Cagree to,=E2=80=9D because =E2=80=
=9Can agreement is not a necessary element of group formation=E2=80=9D:</p>=
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">These amendments would make clear =
that the determination as to whether two or more persons are acting as a gr=
oup does not depend solely on the presence of an express agreement and that=
, depending on the particular facts and circumstances, concerted actions by=
 two or more persons for the purpose of acquiring, holding or disposing of =
securities of an issuer are sufficient to constitute the formation of a gro=
up.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t particular=
ly know what that means, and I don=E2=80=99t think anyone else does either.=
 But it is=C2=A0<em>vaguer=C2=A0</em>than the previous rule, and thus more =
dangerous. In particular: One thing that activists do, when they are trying=
 to make changes at a company, is call up=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>sharehol=
ders =E2=80=94=C2=A0big institutional shareholders who don=E2=80=99t do act=
ivism but who have a lot of votes =E2=80=94=C2=A0and try to persuade them. =
An activist is not going to, like, sign an agreement with BlackRock or Vang=
uard saying that they will work together, but they might try to=C2=A0<em>ta=
lk </em>to BlackRock and say =E2=80=9Cthis is why you should vote with us.=
=E2=80=9D Under the old rules, they could do that. Under the new rules, whe=
re any =E2=80=9Cconcerted actions=E2=80=9D create a group, it might be risk=
ier for BlackRock to talk to activists. Preventing shareholders from talkin=
g to each other is bad for activism. It is also just bad for shareholders: =
If the managers can keep the shareholders separated, then they have more po=
wer to ignore them.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another part of the new=
 rules would =E2=80=9Cspecify that if a person, in advance of filing a Sche=
dule 13D, discloses to any other person that such filing will be made and s=
uch other person acquires securities in the covered class for which the Sch=
edule 13D will be filed, those persons shall be deemed to have formed a gro=
up.=E2=80=9D The SEC refers to this as =E2=80=9Ctipping=E2=80=9D: If I tell=
 you that I=E2=80=99m going to do activism in a stock, and you go buy the s=
tock before I disclose my activism, then that seems unfair to everyone else=
, so the SEC will treat us as=C2=A0a group as a sort of punishment. Again, =
though, this seems designed to scare the BlackRocks of the world away from =
talking to activists: If BlackRock meets with an activist, and the activist=
 says =E2=80=9Cwe were thinking of doing activism in Company X, what do you=
 think,=E2=80=9D then is BlackRock locked up from trading in Company X? If =
it=C2=A0buys Company X shares, is it in a group with the activist? What if =
BlackRock puts out a =E2=80=9Crequest for activist=E2=80=9D in Company X?=
=C2=A0If the company=E2=80=99s managers want to fight back against the acti=
vist, can they demand records of everyone the activist talked to in the mon=
th before buying her position? The safer move for big institutional investo=
rs might just be to avoid talking to activists, which will make activism mu=
ch harder.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Overall the effect of these rule=
s seems to be to stop activists from (1) making money from activism and (2)=
 talking to other shareholders. And so there will be less activism, and cor=
porate managers will have more ability to do what they want without listeni=
ng to shareholders.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is weird! We=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27137501.259601/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDMtMjIvdGhl=
LXNlYy13aWxsLXJlZ3VsYXRlLWNsaW1hdGU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyNDIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXR=
tX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwMzI0JnV0bV=
9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3a1a1868" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talk=
ed this week</a> about the SEC=E2=80=99s huge new proposed climate disclosu=
re regime for public companies. Basically shareholders of public companies =
increasingly pressure them to do better on environmental, social and govern=
ance issues, and the SEC has decided that that is good. So it is helping sh=
areholders get some of what they want from companies (climate disclosure), =
and=C2=A0giving the shareholders more tools to pressure the companies to do=
 more of what they want (lower emissions, etc.). At the same time, though, =
it is reducing shareholders=E2=80=99 ability to=C2=A0<em>actually pressure =
companies:=C2=A0</em>It is making activism harder, which makes it easier fo=
r corporate managers to ignore shareholders. The shareholders can have the =
ESG things that the SEC wants, but not the ESG things that they want.</p><t=
